  "instructions": [
    "Soak the Idli rice for 4 hours.",
    "Drain the rice and blend it into a smooth batter with the yeast-free dosa batter mix and water.",
    "Add the chopped strawberries, green chilies, cilantro, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper to the batter and mix well.",
    "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and add 1 tablespoon of coconut oil.",
    "Pour a small ladle of the batter onto the pan and spread it evenly to form a dosa.",
    "Cook for 2 minutes on the first side and flip it over.",
    "Cook for another 2 minutes on the second side.",
    "Repeat with the remaining batter to make 8-10 dosas.",
    "Serve the dosas hot with a dollop of ghee, a sprinkle of cilantro, and a side of Jain-friendly paneer cheese alternative (if using)."
  ],
